# Array Practice Questions

## 1. Sum of Array
Input:
5
1 2 3 4 5

Expected Output:
Sum = 15

---

## 2. Largest Element
Input:
5
10 40 20 80 30

Expected Output:
Largest = 80

---

## 3. Smallest Element
Input:
5
10 40 20 80 30

Expected Output:
Smallest = 10

---

## 4. Linear Search
Input:
5
10 20 30 40 50
30

Expected Output:
Element found at index 2

---

## 5. Reverse Array
Input:
5
1 2 3 4 5

Expected Output:
5 4 3 2 1

---

## 6. Check Sorted Array
Input:
5
1 2 3 4 5

Expected Output:
Sorted

---

## 7. Second Largest Element
Input:
5
10 50 20 80 30

Expected Output:
Second Largest = 50

---

## 8. Frequency Count
Input:
5
1 2 2 3 1

Expected Output:
1 -> 2
2 -> 2
3 -> 1

---

## 9. Move All Zeros to End
Input:
7
1 0 2 0 3 4 0

Expected Output:
1 2 3 4 0 0 0

---

## 10. Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array
Input:
7
1 1 2 2 3 3 4

Expected Output:
1 2 3 4

---

## 11. Rotate Array by K
Input:
5
1 2 3 4 5
2

Expected Output:
4 5 1 2 3

---

## 12. Prefix Sum
Input:
5
1 2 3 4 5

Expected Output:
1 3 6 10 15

---

## 13. Range Sum Query
Input:
5
1 2 3 4 5
1 3

Expected Output:
Range Sum = 9

---

## 14. Maximum Sum of K Consecutive Elements
Input:
6
1 8 30 -5 20 7
3

Expected Output:
Maximum Sum = 45

---

## 15. Stock Buy and Sell - One Transaction
Input:
6
7 1 5 3 6 4

Expected Output:
Maximum Profit = 5

---

## 16. Stock Buy and Sell - Multiple Transactions
Input:
6
7 1 5 3 6 4

Expected Output:
Maximum Profit = 7

---

## 17. Leaders in Array
Input:
6
16 17 4 3 5 2

Expected Output:
17 5 2

---

## 18. Two Sum
Input:
4
2 7 11 15
9

Expected Output:
Indices = 0 1
---------------------------------- TIME AND SPACE COMPLEXCITY OF ARRAY PROBLEMS 
Day 1
Sum of Array
Pattern: Traversal
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Largest Element
Pattern: Keep Best So Far
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Smallest Element
Pattern: Keep Minimum So Far
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Day 2
Linear Search
Pattern: Traversal/Search
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Reverse Array
Pattern: Two Pointers
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Check Sorted Array
Pattern: Adjacent Comparison
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Second Largest Element
Pattern: Keep Largest + Second Largest
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Intermediate Arrays
Selection Sort
Pattern: Find Minimum and Swap
TC: O(n²)
SC: O(1)
Frequency Count
Pattern: Nested Loop Counting
TC: O(n²)
SC: O(1)
Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array
Pattern: Two Pointers
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Move All Zeros to End
Pattern: Two Pointers / Stable Partition
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Rotate Array by K
Pattern: Index Mapping
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)
Prefix Sum & Sliding Window
Prefix Sum
Pattern: Preprocessing
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)
Maximum Sum of K Consecutive Elements
Pattern: Sliding Window
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Advanced Array Patterns
Stock Buy and Sell (One Transaction)
Pattern: Track Minimum So Far
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Stock Buy and Sell (Multiple Transactions)
Pattern: Greedy
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Leaders in Array
Pattern: Right-to-Left Traversal
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Two Sum
Brute Force:
TC: O(n²)
SC: O(1)
Hash Map:
TC: O(n)
SC: O(n)
Not Fully Completed Yet
Kadane's Algorithm (Maximum Subarray Sum)
Pattern: Dynamic Programming / Running Sum
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)
Majority Element
Pattern: Boyer-Moore Voting
TC: O(n)
SC: O(1)

